cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving the performance of style transfer models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes extensions to existing models, which involves training and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of multilingual and feedback-based back translation techniques also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed extensions using various metrics, indicating the possibility of it belonging to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
